    <arm_group_type>Active Comparator</arm_group_type>
    <description>At enrollment, patients will be randomized to ranolazine or placebo. In the active drug arm each patient will be started on a 500 mg twice a day dose for one week with subsequent increase to 1000 mg twice a day at end of first week. For patients on anti-arrhythmic therapy at the time of randomization, their ECG will be checked at end of first week on 500 mg dose and again at end of second week on 1000 mg dose. For patients with CrCl &lt;60ml/min prior to randomization, their CrCl will be checked again at 2 weeks and study drug discontinued if &lt;30ml/min. For patients with CrCl &lt;60ml/min at 2 weeks, their CrCl will be checked again at 4 weeks and study drug discontinued if &lt;30ml/min.</description>
